<|startoftext|>I am only rating the location with the lack of a restaurant\/bar. We drove here from Phoenix to Los Angeles based on a friend's recommendation and it was a real drag to get there late. However, it was totally worth it. We arrived at the club around 11am on Saturday night and were able to get a table right away. \n\nWe arrived to a relatively quiet club, which is awesome for a Friday night, sans the usual run-down of club life. We were seated at a table right off the dance floor and the bartender was on top of everything, making sure to check on us constantly, which really helped with the vibe. \n\nBefore getting into the GOODNESS, let's talk about the DRINKS. The drinks here are ridiculously great especially the mojito. Their drinks are served with ice and aren't overly sweet. Their teas are also served with ice and aren't overly sweet. Our server was extremely fast and attentive. I didn't drink but I would definitely ask my server to serve me one of those beers I love to drink and get ice and water throughout the evening.\n\nThe dancing\/litmus class was fun. The drinks aren't too strong especially the margaritas. The shots are fun and sweet and not so strong. If you get drinks, keep in mind they are a small amount so get a group of 4 unless you're huge. \n\nThe food was amazing. We had the shrimp tostada to start and its huge even though it's only about an order (about half a head). My friend had the chimichanga and she took home 2 portions. The chimichanga wasn't too heavy especially if you can get a bowl. The shrimp was perfectly cooked and seasoned. The tostada was also good especially if you stick with one as it is. The meatballs are the best in town and you know you're receiving them a treat. The pastor was excellent and very much enjoyed the meal. We also had the steak platter which was so awesome and large portions.\n\nNot many, if any, tables were covered in mirrors and I mean they're covered in mirrors in order to dance. I would love to be in there dancing with a drink in one hand while covering your face with the other, but the club itself seemed enough closed off so we probably didn't get free mirrors. \n\nThe music is pretty chill and the staff was chill and laid back- it makes for a good place to bring the family especially if you've got a few young ones. Good vibes and good time.<|endoftext|>
